,Recommended,260130,9857766,"Posted: 17 April, 2014",all,Kuronare,"What is Agarest: Generations of War Zero? Agarest, is a game set in the world of Agarest. Simple, right? It is a world ridden with war between the Evil and the Light gods. You start the game in the middle of this war as Commander Zeeg~ (Sieghart.) Who soon finds himself at the feet of an evil Larva, a minor god. Events unfold and Zeeg~ is given the power to defeat this foe.  I am not going to spoil much, but it is almost exactly like what happened to Leonhart from the first game.Agarest is a SRPG, Stratagey Roleplaying Game. The battle system is turned based. So if you do not like turn based games well, I am sorry. This game may not be for you. This title also introduces several new features its predecessor didn't, like the Free Intention system and Extra mode. Extra mode is for people who have played the previous installment in the franchise, Agarest: Generations of War and the Free Intention system is another relationship builder. It will sometimes give items, new CGs, and costumes for your party to use. Also they added in the Action Animation System that allows the characters to move their lips during cutscenes. It is pretty neat for the time the game was actually released, 2009, but for todays standards it is pretty mediocre.If you were expecting to have 30+ characters like in this first game you will be disappointed. This game only contains two genertaions unlike the previous five, and there are only fiften members that you will be finding in your party. However I do not think this detracts from the game in any way whatsoever. The game is still 80+ hours, like its predecessor and the story is very immersive.Overall - I really enjoy playing the game. If you are a fan of Disgaea or Fire Emblem I thnk you will find this game different with the added relationship systems. 8/10."
