,Recommended,260130,15640725,"Posted: 1 May, 2015",all,TheCyclingNut,"I am so glad that devs from Japan have decided to release more of their games to the PC market. This is one game in the Generations series and is a prequel to the first game in the series. However you can jump into this game regardless if you have played any games in the series.The graphics are just beautiful and vibrant on PC, it has full controller support but I do not recommend using it. The game is simple enough that even a console convert like me prefered playing it with the M & K.The main reason is using the controller in the battle scenes is just plain awkward and frustrating to say the least. The game is very grinding natured so if you prefer to just run through in a linear way I would suggest Kingdoms of Amalur or something like that. This is a Japaneese RPG thru and through, so prepare to grind a lot.One real downside to the game is the sheer lack of varied arenas, they use only a handfull for all of the battles which is sad. So if your are thinking mid way in a battle man I seen this before, you have.That said it is still worth it to pick it up, though I would when in a sale or featured game. While it is a quality made game I still feel the $20 + price tag is to high given the ridiculous cost of the DLC. That high price of the DLC is a bad trademark of the entire series to be honest.All in all I give the game a solid 7.5/10 I have to make a few points off for the lack of variance in the battle arenas, thee awkward camera controll, and the high cost of the DLC and game."
